title: For Sale:  Tactical 12 ga. 17-Rds.
postcontent: Impressed by reviews that I saw on this shotgun and having owned the Mossberg 500 and 590A1 as well as the Winchester 1300 Defender in the past, I purchased this a little over one year ago and have been happy ever since.  Funding another project, I am sacrificing this home defense shotgun for the cause.  I have put over 300 rounds through this weapon without a single hiccup.  It is the Stevens 320 tactical shotgun, 12-ga with 18.5" barrel.  I have installed a synthetic barrel shroud that is made specifically not to heat up during rapid firing.  It carries a Choate Machine & Tool Co. x1 rd. magazine extension, bringing it from a 5-rd. tube magazine to x6-rds. total.  Because of the design of the extended pump handle, one cannot install a sidesaddle shell holder on the left-hand side of the receiver.  To address this, I mounted on each side of the buttstock, a x5-rd. shell holder, providing 10 rounds of firepower at the ready.  Please note that this is a very solid but hollow buttstock, so having added the additional 10 rounds to the buttstock does not add great amount of weight to this firearm.  It is very pleasingly balanced and is tactfully sound.  With a round in the chamber, you are talking a total of seventeen (17) rounds with this now formitable shotgun.  Also installed is a hi-viz front sight (with this purchase will come the other varying colored front site tubes to change the color as you so desire).  Additionally, also mounted on this tactical shotgun is a 150 lumen spotlight with varying apeture.  This is an incredibly bright light that is a must in a tactical situation and turns the darkness into daylight.I am selling this for $300 and no less, as it it well worth it.  I would not part with this but again, am funding another project.  ***Forgive me for putting "Winchester" for the mfg. of this shotgun.  I did so, as it most closely resembles a Winchester 1300 with the safety on the trigger guard.
